        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-joyce-anelay' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0650P0_20030701_GCR_294' title='Link to this speech by Ms Joyce Anelay' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-joyce-anelay" title="Ms Joyce Anelay">Baroness Anelay of St Johns</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            1 am grateful to the Minister for his helpful explanation. It is always useful to know that Opposition amendments cause the Government to look with renewed vigour at their own
            
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_225gc' title='Col. 225GC &mdash; HL Deb 01 July 2003 vol 650 c225GC' name='column_225gc' href='#column_225gc' rel='bookmark'>225GC</a>
            Bills. We look forward to even more vigorous action from him in the future. I beg leave to withdraw the amendment.
          </p>
